cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.CR

This paper discusses the design and evaluation of an adaptive cooperative scheme for aerial-terrestrial communication networks. The paper focuses on improving energy efficiency and real-time applications, which are relevant to the fields of networked systems (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), multi-agent systems (cs.MA), control systems (cs.SY), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, since the paper primarily deals with communication networks, we believe that cs.NI is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.IT and cs.MA. The other two sub-categories, cs.SY and cs.CR, are less likely but still possible given the paper's focus on energy-efficient and secure communication.
